83
00:06:50,416 --> 00:06:51,666
That nearly killed me.

84
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:53,500
Why'd you chase me?

85
00:06:53,583 --> 00:06:54,458
Damn!

86
00:06:54,541 --> 00:06:56,833
Stupid sore feet!

87
00:06:56,916 --> 00:06:58,041
Give it!

88
00:06:58,125 --> 00:06:59,666
Now don't you start crying.

89
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:01,416
Be a man.

90
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:04,333
Is this really all you took?

91
00:07:04,416 --> 00:07:05,875
Just small potatoes.

92
00:07:05,958 --> 00:07:08,666
You're taking
this back with me.

93
00:07:08,750 --> 00:07:11,500
You can accept that, right?

94
00:07:11,583 --> 00:07:14,041
Can't you trust
that I know what's best?

95
00:07:17,291 --> 00:07:20,250
Listen, kid, I was your
age once, too, you know.

96
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:23,375
I really don't like seein'
you this miserable.

97
00:07:26,375 --> 00:07:27,875
Come on, stand up.

98
00:07:27,958 --> 00:07:29,583
Let's go.

99
00:07:44,791 --> 00:07:46,208
Dammit!

100
00:07:46,291 --> 00:07:49,416
If you want in, smile
and tell me you're sorry.

101
00:07:49,500 --> 00:07:50,958
Those are my terms.

102
00:08:00,166 --> 00:08:02,000
And that was a look
at former pro bullfighter

103
00:08:02,083 --> 00:08:04,583
and Marco's father-in-law,
Arnaldo Santoro...

104
00:08:04,666 --> 00:08:05,625
She's gone.

105
00:08:05,708 --> 00:08:08,666
Hatchin has been kidnapped.

106
00:08:08,750 --> 00:08:10,041
I know it's Fantasma.

107
00:08:10,125 --> 00:08:11,750
Can you tell me
where they took her?

108
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:12,791
No can do.

109
00:08:12,875 --> 00:08:13,875
Ivan, please.

110
00:08:13,958 --> 00:08:16,833
I said "no can do,"
all right?

111
00:08:16,916 --> 00:08:18,708
You planning to
go there alone?

112
00:08:18,791 --> 00:08:20,875
And how do you
think that's gonna work out?

113
00:08:20,958 --> 00:08:22,833
They still got
plenty of muscle left.

114
00:08:22,916 --> 00:08:24,250
You show up and-- Pop!

115
00:08:24,333 --> 00:08:24,958
Pop!

116
00:08:25,041 --> 00:08:25,833
Pop!

117
00:08:25,916 --> 00:08:27,375
You're swiss cheese.

118
00:08:27,458 --> 00:08:29,125
Besides I'm sure she's okay.

119
00:08:29,208 --> 00:08:31,500
They're not gonna
kill her at this point.

120
00:08:31,583 --> 00:08:33,791
Least, not until
they've got you.

121
00:08:33,875 --> 00:08:36,750
Honestly, I couldn't
help you anyway.

122
00:08:36,833 --> 00:08:38,791
I dunno where they are.

123
00:08:38,875 --> 00:08:41,541
Though, if you wandered the
streets flapping your arms

124
00:08:41,625 --> 00:08:43,666
saying, "Here I am,
it's Michiko,"

125
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:45,833
I'm sure they'd come to you.

126
00:08:45,916 --> 00:08:46,875
Wait!

127
00:08:46,958 --> 00:08:48,291
I'm joking,
please don't do that.

128
00:08:48,375 --> 00:08:51,291
But seriously, tomorrow's
your day to strike.

129
00:08:51,375 --> 00:08:55,333
Marco's gonna be
fighting Romão the Fourth.

130
00:08:55,416 --> 00:08:57,416
If they're using
Hatchin as their trump,

131
00:08:57,500 --> 00:09:00,416
you're gonna need a damn
high card of your own.

132
00:09:00,500 --> 00:09:03,041
You remember their leader,
don't you?

133
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:04,583
It's Vasily Nabokov.

134
00:09:04,666 --> 00:09:07,375
That eager errand boy
Kiril took under his wing.

135
00:09:07,458 --> 00:09:08,208
No.

136
00:09:08,291 --> 00:09:09,375
Don't recall.

137
00:09:09,458 --> 00:09:11,458
Well, he's a big,
long-haired fatty now,

138
00:09:11,541 --> 00:09:13,125
so look for him
at the bull fight.

139
00:09:13,208 --> 00:09:14,875
He's always there.

140
00:09:17,791 --> 00:09:18,333
'Kay.

141
00:09:18,416 --> 00:09:19,416
I let you come in.

142
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:22,208
Now smile and tell me
you're sorry.

143
00:09:22,291 --> 00:09:23,375
Yeah, uh.

144
00:09:23,458 --> 00:09:24,625
Sorry.

145
00:09:24,708 --> 00:09:25,833
Huh?

146
00:09:25,916 --> 00:09:26,791
What's that?

147
00:09:26,875 --> 00:09:29,833
I don't think I heard you.

148
00:09:29,916 --> 00:09:31,000
I'm sorry.

149
00:09:31,083 --> 00:09:32,958
Okay?

150
00:09:33,041 --> 00:09:33,833
Yeah.

151
00:09:33,916 --> 00:09:34,791
Okay.

152
00:09:34,875 --> 00:09:36,250
We're good.

153
00:09:41,125 --> 00:09:42,541
Thank you.

154
00:09:42,625 --> 00:09:44,041
He carries those hopes and
dreams as tomorrow's showdown

155
00:09:44,125 --> 00:09:45,541
quickly approaches.

156
00:09:45,625 --> 00:09:48,750
Ms. Zelia Bastos, who even today
still checks in on Marco,

157
00:09:48,833 --> 00:09:50,083
had this to say:

158
00:09:50,166 --> 00:09:52,750
Well. Good luck and be careful.

159
00:09:56,791 --> 00:09:58,458
What's so funny?

160
00:09:58,541 --> 00:10:01,583
It's nothin',
sorry, forget it.

161
00:10:01,666 --> 00:10:03,958
You gotta be kiddin' me.

162
00:10:17,208 --> 00:10:19,000
You are hungry, yes?

163
00:10:24,625 --> 00:10:27,375
Is good to stop and
smell the roses sometimes.

164
00:10:27,458 --> 00:10:28,833
Ah.

165
00:10:28,916 --> 00:10:31,750
Most of these bulls
are tough and no good.

166
00:10:31,833 --> 00:10:35,125
But you, Shirkov the Third.

167
00:10:35,208 --> 00:10:38,458
You are so delicious
I could cry like child!

168
00:10:43,083 --> 00:10:45,041
So what are you to that woman?

169
00:10:45,125 --> 00:10:46,458
Huh?

170
00:10:46,541 --> 00:10:48,375
Her daughter?

171
00:10:48,458 --> 00:10:50,125
Who am I to who?

172
00:10:50,208 --> 00:10:50,750
Ugh.

173
00:10:50,833 --> 00:10:52,375
Michiko Malandro.

174
00:10:52,458 --> 00:10:54,250
Michiko Malandro.

175
00:10:54,333 --> 00:10:55,375
Michiko!

176
00:10:55,458 --> 00:10:56,541
Michiko!

177
00:10:56,625 --> 00:10:57,333
Michiko!

178
00:10:57,416 --> 00:10:58,041
Michiko!

179
00:10:58,125 --> 00:10:59,750
Michiko!

180
00:11:01,250 --> 00:11:04,250
Sorry about that.

181
00:11:04,333 --> 00:11:05,833
What is your name then?

182
00:11:05,916 --> 00:11:07,375
Hana Morenos.

183
00:11:07,458 --> 00:11:08,708
Morenos.

184
00:11:08,791 --> 00:11:11,208
Not related to
Hiroshi Morenos are you?

185
00:11:11,291 --> 00:11:13,666
I'm not sure,
but supposedly he's my dad.

186
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:14,541
Wait a minute.

187
00:11:14,625 --> 00:11:16,333
Didn't he die a long time ago?

188
00:11:16,416 --> 00:11:17,333
Yeah.

189
00:11:17,416 --> 00:11:20,916
Don't ask me
to explain the math.

190
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:23,000
Yeah all right,
whatever you say.

191
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:26,000
How can meat taste this good?

192
00:11:26,083 --> 00:11:28,875
It's one of the
wonders of the world.

193
00:11:28,958 --> 00:11:30,458
So, Hana-yenka.

194
00:11:30,541 --> 00:11:32,500
Hana what?

195
00:11:32,583 --> 00:11:34,416
Michiko will come
for you, right?

196
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:37,250
Friends are important and we
must do what we can for them.

197
00:11:37,333 --> 00:11:39,291
That is what I believe.

198
00:11:39,375 --> 00:11:42,541
Phone call, Mr. Vasily, sir.

199
00:11:42,625 --> 00:11:43,500
What is it?

200
00:11:43,583 --> 00:11:45,625
It's Mr. Satoshi, sir.

201
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:49,375
Hello!

202
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:51,125
What's going on, Fatso?

203
00:11:51,208 --> 00:11:53,750
You tryin' to fuck me over?

204
00:11:53,833 --> 00:11:57,750
I still haven't got my cut from
any of you Fantasma shitheads.

205
00:11:57,833 --> 00:11:58,666
What's that about?

206
00:11:58,750 --> 00:12:00,083
You turning on me?

207
00:12:00,166 --> 00:12:03,416
No sir! Of course not!
Our bulls just keep losing.

208
00:12:03,500 --> 00:12:06,625
You're a real strip.

209
00:12:06,708 --> 00:12:07,250
Strip?

210
00:12:07,333 --> 00:12:08,416
Of bacon, stupid.

211
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:09,583
Use your brain.

212
00:12:09,666 --> 00:12:11,666
You're breathing hard,
something wrong?

213
00:12:11,750 --> 00:12:14,041
Too much lard
dripping out your ass?

214
00:12:14,125 --> 00:12:15,208
No.

215
00:12:15,291 --> 00:12:16,708
I'll have it all ready
by tomorrow night,

216
00:12:16,791 --> 00:12:17,750
in one lump sum.

217
00:12:17,833 --> 00:12:19,333
God damn right, ham hock!

218
00:12:19,416 --> 00:12:20,250
I will, sir.

219
00:12:20,333 --> 00:12:21,291
One more thing.

220
00:12:21,375 --> 00:12:23,666
Michiko Milandro's turned up.

221
00:12:23,750 --> 00:12:27,333
Do we have permission to
take care of her ourselves?

222
00:12:27,416 --> 00:12:29,625
I'm not saying this makes up
for it, but we'll send her

223
00:12:29,708 --> 00:12:32,541
along with the money
as a present.

224
00:12:32,625 --> 00:12:34,125
A present, huh?

225
00:12:34,208 --> 00:12:35,541
Da.

226
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,625
Still haven't seen anyone
who looks like Michiko, sir.

227
00:12:48,708 --> 00:12:49,541
Keep looking!

228
00:12:49,625 --> 00:12:50,958
Find the bitch!

229
00:12:51,041 --> 00:12:52,291
Moving the kid now.

230
00:12:52,375 --> 00:12:54,333
We'll leave soon
as we get the money.

231
00:12:54,416 --> 00:12:55,500
Good.

232
00:12:55,583 --> 00:12:56,916
Just make sure to tell
that idiot Satoshi

233
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,458
you're on your way.

234
00:12:58,541 --> 00:13:00,166
Snipers are ready, boss.

235
00:13:00,250 --> 00:13:02,416
Recheck those silencers again.

236
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:05,458
And when you hit Marco,
make sure it's a kill shot.

237
00:13:05,541 --> 00:13:08,291
Marco Bussi Santoro faces
the biggest challenge yet

238
00:13:08,375 --> 00:13:11,250
in his stellar career;
the bloodthirsty demon bull,

239
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:12,500
Romão the Fourth!

240
00:13:12,583 --> 00:13:14,208
Coming up next!

241
00:13:18,875 --> 00:13:19,833
Inspection time.

242
00:13:19,916 --> 00:13:21,208
Open up the back.

243
00:13:21,291 --> 00:13:25,041
This is just our usual
scheduled delivery sir.

244
00:13:25,125 --> 00:13:26,791
Then your permits, too.

245
00:13:36,208 --> 00:13:37,250
Well?

246
00:13:37,333 --> 00:13:39,041
It looks okay.

247
00:13:40,708 --> 00:13:43,666
I thought we were
dead for sure.

248
00:13:43,750 --> 00:13:45,958
