and nasty in here!

249
00:13:46,041 --> 00:13:49,625
Oh, quitcher bitchin' princess,
I told you I washed it out.

250
00:13:49,708 --> 00:13:50,833
Let's go.

251
00:14:05,291 --> 00:14:06,791
--Mich--
--Quiet!

252
00:14:10,041 --> 00:14:11,291
Are you crazy?

253
00:14:20,041 --> 00:14:21,500
Once we're in the kitchen
we'll dress you up like

254
00:14:21,583 --> 00:14:23,583
a concession girl, then
you can roam the stands

255
00:14:23,666 --> 00:14:26,208
with no problem.

256
00:14:26,291 --> 00:14:27,791
Michiko?

257
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:37,458
Looky what I found.

258
00:14:43,875 --> 00:14:44,583
Wait bro!

259
00:14:44,666 --> 00:14:46,000
Don't shoot!

260
00:14:52,958 --> 00:14:53,791
Ivan!

261
00:14:53,875 --> 00:14:55,041
Get down!

262
00:14:55,125 --> 00:14:55,916
Huh?

263
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:56,625
What?

264
00:14:56,708 --> 00:14:58,458
I said get down, now!

265
00:15:04,625 --> 00:15:05,833
Get that bitch!

266
00:15:15,083 --> 00:15:16,750
What's the Michiko situation?

267
00:15:16,833 --> 00:15:18,291
Nobody's seen her!

268
00:15:18,375 --> 00:15:19,541
What?

269
00:15:21,125 --> 00:15:24,000
This is it, folks, the moment
we've all been waiting for!

270
00:15:24,083 --> 00:15:25,875
The smiling young prince
has entered the ring,

271
00:15:25,958 --> 00:15:27,416
giving a hearty
response to his fans.

272
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:28,666
But what's this?

273
00:15:28,750 --> 00:15:30,875
Marco is wearing a mask!

274
00:15:30,958 --> 00:15:34,375
What could be motivating this
unexpected theatrical flair?

275
00:15:34,458 --> 00:15:36,625
Whatever prompted it, the
choice seems well-received,

276
00:15:36,708 --> 00:15:40,166
as he's got the entire
crowd on their feet!

277
00:15:40,250 --> 00:15:42,458
And now from the
opposite end of the arena,

278
00:15:42,541 --> 00:15:44,583
we're seeing
Marco's challenger,

279
00:15:44,666 --> 00:15:47,833
the indomitable
Romão the Fourth!

280
00:15:56,958 --> 00:15:58,875
Romão leaps into action!

281
00:15:58,958 --> 00:16:01,166
And Marco sidesteps cleanly!

282
00:16:03,875 --> 00:16:07,583
Again Romão lunges,
and Marco narrowly evades!

283
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:17,125
A dirty trick from Marco!

284
00:16:17,208 --> 00:16:19,708
He takes full advantage of
the move and spears the bull!

285
00:16:19,791 --> 00:16:23,541
But no, it doesn't stick!

286
00:16:23,625 --> 00:16:26,125
An uncharacteristically
disgraceful retreat,

287
00:16:26,208 --> 00:16:28,208
and Marco has
left himself open.

288
00:16:28,291 --> 00:16:30,958
His cloak and mask
have come off and-- wait!

289
00:16:31,041 --> 00:16:32,833
That isn't Marco at all!

290
00:16:32,916 --> 00:16:34,166
It's a woman!

291
00:16:34,250 --> 00:16:36,791
The matador is
an unknown female!

292
00:16:36,875 --> 00:16:39,333
There's a cacophony
of boos from the audience!

293
00:16:39,416 --> 00:16:40,375
That's it, folks.

294
00:16:40,458 --> 00:16:43,208
No wagers will
be honored now!

295
00:16:43,291 --> 00:16:44,208
Yeah that's her!

296
00:16:44,291 --> 00:16:46,125
Target is the matador!

297
00:16:57,916 --> 00:17:00,291
The unknown woman
faces Romão.

298
00:17:00,375 --> 00:17:01,375
She spears him!

299
00:17:01,458 --> 00:17:02,833
She actually spears him!

300
00:17:02,916 --> 00:17:04,416
A surprising turn!

301
00:17:04,500 --> 00:17:06,666
A cheer swells up
from the crowd!

302
00:17:10,166 --> 00:17:11,958
She's taking a sword now?

303
00:17:12,041 --> 00:17:13,916
All customs are
out the window!

304
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,916
And that's the problem
with amateurs!

305
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:17,166
Where's Michiko?

306
00:17:17,250 --> 00:17:18,541
 Is she here?

307
00:17:20,833 --> 00:17:22,208
Damn it!

308
00:17:24,125 --> 00:17:25,541
She needs my help!

309
00:17:25,625 --> 00:17:27,208
Cut these ropes!

310
00:17:31,916 --> 00:17:34,041
She's clearly
distracted by something.

311
00:17:34,125 --> 00:17:35,583
I'm sure I'm not
the only fan wishing

312
00:17:35,666 --> 00:17:37,625
she'd focus on the fight.

313
00:17:42,041 --> 00:17:43,875
But now she turns
to face Romão!

314
00:17:43,958 --> 00:17:45,750
We could have ourselves
a bout after all!

315
00:17:45,833 --> 00:17:46,708
What?

316
00:17:46,791 --> 00:17:48,083
Oh!

317
00:17:48,166 --> 00:17:49,666
She leaps into the air,
using Romão as a kickboard

318
00:17:49,750 --> 00:17:52,833
to launch into the stands!

319
00:17:52,916 --> 00:17:55,750
Has she come this far
just to surrender?

320
00:18:01,666 --> 00:18:04,750
It's been a hundred years
since we met here last, Michiko.

321
00:18:04,833 --> 00:18:06,500
Seriously, a hundred years?

322
00:18:06,583 --> 00:18:09,041
I'm all for exaggeration,
but come on!

323
00:18:13,041 --> 00:18:14,750
This is what you
call sword fighting?

324
00:18:14,833 --> 00:18:16,416
Not exactly graceful.

325
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:18,041
You'll die all the same.

326
00:18:18,125 --> 00:18:19,666
Oh, now I remember you.

327
00:18:19,750 --> 00:18:22,166
Little Vasily,
the errand boy!

328
00:18:25,875 --> 00:18:27,750
Michiko, horosho!

329
00:18:27,833 --> 00:18:30,291
The entire stadium is
erupting in excitement over

330
00:18:30,375 --> 00:18:32,291
a second surprise performer!

331
00:18:32,375 --> 00:18:35,541
It appears to be a young girl
armed only with a ladle!

332
00:18:35,625 --> 00:18:37,291
Romão has locked
onto her quickly...

333
00:18:37,375 --> 00:18:40,458
What in the world are
those two doing in there?

334
00:18:50,375 --> 00:18:52,458
Do svidaniya, Michiko!

335
00:18:55,125 --> 00:18:57,833
I got ya now, Vasily.

336
00:18:57,916 --> 00:18:59,833
Tell me where Hatchin is!

337
00:18:59,916 --> 00:19:03,541
Should be well on her way to
that dumb-shit Satoshi by now.

338
00:19:06,875 --> 00:19:08,125
Oh crap.

339
00:19:13,458 --> 00:19:14,916
Use that.

340
00:19:18,291 --> 00:19:19,541
What are you idiots
waiting for?

341
00:19:19,625 --> 00:19:21,875
Come down here and help me!

342
00:19:21,958 --> 00:19:23,625
Shoot the bull!

343
00:19:28,583 --> 00:19:30,291
What are you doing down there?

344
00:19:30,375 --> 00:19:32,666
I'm on my way,
don't let it getcha!

345
00:19:36,333 --> 00:19:38,708
No no no no no no no no no!

346
00:19:38,791 --> 00:19:41,125
Why can't you just sit still
like a good hostage?

347
00:19:41,208 --> 00:19:42,500
Oh shut up!

348
00:19:42,583 --> 00:19:43,958
Grab on!

349
00:19:45,291 --> 00:19:45,833
Damn it!

350
00:19:45,916 --> 00:19:47,000
Come back!

351
00:19:47,083 --> 00:19:48,208
I can't!

352
00:19:49,750 --> 00:19:51,250
Hatchin, get up!

353
00:19:53,041 --> 00:19:54,000
Over here!

354
00:19:54,083 --> 00:19:55,291
Run!

355
00:20:05,416 --> 00:20:08,083
Um, let's get while
the gettin's good!

356
00:20:13,625 --> 00:20:15,125
You okay?

357
00:20:19,208 --> 00:20:21,458
Stop lookin'
for trouble you don't need.

358
00:20:21,541 --> 00:20:24,416
What'd you expect me
to do Michiko?

359
00:20:24,500 --> 00:20:26,333
I don't want you to die.

360
00:20:26,416 --> 00:20:28,083
Hey, I won't.

361
00:20:28,166 --> 00:20:30,791
But thank you.

362
00:20:33,208 --> 00:20:35,625
The mystery woman has
rescued the ladle girl,

363
00:20:35,708 --> 00:20:38,708
and seems to have no interest
in continuing the bullfight.

364
00:20:38,791 --> 00:20:41,166
We're just getting word now
that Marco has been found

365
00:20:41,250 --> 00:20:42,291
in his dressing room...

366
00:20:42,375 --> 00:20:44,041
I suppose I should feel lucky.

367
00:20:44,125 --> 00:20:46,708
No more "express
train to hell."

368
00:20:51,166 --> 00:20:53,375
So you're actually
planning to visit Satoshi?

369
00:20:53,458 --> 00:20:54,666
Yup.

370
00:20:54,750 --> 00:20:56,000
Unbelievable.

371
00:20:56,083 --> 00:20:58,291
The word is,
Satoshi's in Osso.

372
00:20:58,375 --> 00:21:00,083
But it's a nest
for unfriendlies

373
00:21:00,166 --> 00:21:02,625
so he's supposedly
gone underground.

374
00:21:04,666 --> 00:21:05,708
Understood.

375
00:21:05,791 --> 00:21:07,208
Thanks for that.

376
00:21:10,375 --> 00:21:12,916
We'll be back.

377
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,416
Don't get yourselves killed!

